Now I see the crucial piece! In MathJax 3, there was a fix (PR #307) where the attribute name was changed from `'href'` to `'xlink:href'` when creating `<use>` elements. This was because:

- When using `setAttributeNS(XLINKNS, 'href', id)`, WebKit/Safari serialized it incorrectly as `NS1:href` or similar
- The fix was to use `setAttributeNS(XLINKNS, 'xlink:href', id)`, which WebKit serializes correctly

Now let me check what MathJax 4 does. Looking at the code I found earlier:```typescript


// MathJax 4 (from MathJax-src master)
protected useNode(variant: string, C: string, path: string): N {  const use = this.svg('use', { 'data-c': C });
  const id = '#' + this.jax.fontCache.cachePath(variant, C, path);  this.adaptor.setAttribute(
    use,    'href',    id,
    this.jax.options.useXlink ? XLINKNS : null
  );
  return use;
}```

