InterestingMathJax 4 reverted back to using `'href'` as the attribute name, but now it conditionally passes the namespace based on the `useXlink` option, so it can use either the plain `href` attribute or the namespaced version depending on the configuration. So the adaptor does construct `'xlink:href'` from the namespace, making the call equivalent to the v3 fix. Let me trace through the actual HTMLAdaptor source code on GitHub to verify this is what's really happening.

